IDefaultGridElementManager, IGridContainer, IGridElement, IGridElementManager, IGridModelNotifier, IStorableElementManager, IVoManager, org.eclipse.core.runtime.IAdaptable
public class VoManager
extends AbstractDefaultGridElementManager
implements IVoManager

Internal implementation of the IVoManager interface. This is not intended to be accessible from the outside. Instead the GridModel.getVoManager() method should be used. This class is used as a singleton.

canManage

public boolean canManage(IGridElement element)
Description copied from interface: IGridElementManager
Determines if this manager is able to manage the specified grid element. A manager is always dedicated to one special type of grid elements so this method has only to return true for this special type and its subtypes.

Specified by:
canManage in interface IGridElementManager
Parameters:
element - The element that wants to be managed by this manager.
Returns:
True if the manager is able to manage the specified grid element.

loadElements

public void loadElements()
                  throws GridModelException
Description copied from interface: IStorableElementManager
Load the state of this manager from a predefined location. It is the managers responsibility to determine the location from which to load the state. It is also the managers responsibility how the elements are loaded (one per file or all elements in one big file...). Be aware of the fact that all formerly contained elements are deleted before the managers loads the new elements.

Specified by:
loadElements in interface IStorableElementManager
Throws:
GridModelException - If an error occures during the load operation. This may for example be due to an IOException.

saveElements

public void saveElements()
                  throws GridModelException
Description copied from interface: IStorableElementManager
Save all currently managed elements. It is the managers responsibility to save the elements to an appropriate location. It is also the managers responsibility how the elements should be saved (one per file or all in one big file...).

Specified by:
saveElements in interface IStorableElementManager
Throws:
GridModelException - If an error occures during the save operation. This may for example be due to an IOException.
